/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-010-explorer-002.log:1731:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:50:- Many pressure-Hessian identities are NS-specific in algebraic form while still being non-coercive analytically. The step risks conflating exact NS specificity with usable NS specificity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-010-explorer-002.log:1733:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:74:The central gamble is that a small family of invariant tensor observables can meaningfully constrain the full pressure-Hessian contribution, including harmonic far-field freedom. That is a severe compression step, and the chain does not really justify why it should work beyond hopeful analogy.
