+# Exploration 002 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Screen the main equivalent tensor packagings for the surviving Step-10 family
+menu and decide whether any candidate remains live against the frozen full
+pairing `I_p^far`.
+
+## Method
+
+- Read the Step-10 goal and Step-9 endpoint-freeze materials.
+- Extract the serious surviving family menu after overlap reduction.
+- Compare each live family across documented equivalent tensor packagings.
+- Test whether any packaging yields estimate-level action on the same frozen full
+  pairing, as required by the admission rule.
+
+## Findings Log
+
+### Initialization
+
+- Report skeleton created. Source review in progress.
+
+### Source review completed
+
+- [VERIFIED] `step-009` already froze the only live theorem ledger, the exact
+  endpoint object `I_p^far`, the progress currency
+  (smaller effective coefficient on that same full pairing), the positive-margin
+  threshold, and the immediate-failure / Tao admission rules.
+- [VERIFIED] The serious live menu entering this screen is not broad. The local
+  record keeps only one endpoint-attached `pressure-Hessian / strain-defect`
+  family, with `harmonic-moment cancellation` surviving only as its narrow
+  subquestion rather than as an independent family.
+- [VERIFIED] Run-006 planning already records the main equivalent packagings of
+  that family as pressure-Hessian/strain misalignment, eigenvalue-gap or other
+  invariant combinations of `S`, `omega`-to-eigenframe alignment, and a
+  restricted-Euler defect quantity with remainder, all sitting next to the
+  exact pressure tensor identity and the stretching package.
+- [INFERRED] No repository source shows a packaging-independent, estimate-level
+  shrinkage of the frozen full-pairing coefficient on `I_p^far`.
+- [INFERRED] The first honest Step-10 failure is `repackaging obstruction`:
+  once the remaining line is screened across its documented equivalent
+  packagings, its apparent novelty washes out into known representation,
+  local-geometry, reduced-model, or criterion language without a smaller
+  coefficient on the same full pairing.
+
+## Findings
+
+### 1. Surviving Family Menu After Overlap Reduction
+
+- [VERIFIED] The frozen Step-009 ledger admits no new theorem endpoint here.
+  Step 10 inherits only one endpoint-attached mechanism family:
+  `pressure-Hessian / strain-defect`, and even that family stays alive only if
+  it acts on the same full far-field pairing `I_p^far`. Sources:
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-009/RESULTS.md`
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-009/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-009-exploration-001-endpoint-menu-freeze.md`
+- [VERIFIED] `harmonic-moment cancellation` is not a separate admitted family.
+  It survives only as the narrow subquestion of whether pressure-tensor
+  structure can cancel the affine-and-higher harmonic moments that generate the
+  bad coefficient in the same frozen pairing. Sources:
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-009/RESULTS.md`
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-009/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+  - `library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/pressure-tensor-identity-remains-only-a-narrow-testable-possibility.md`
+- [VERIFIED] `full stretching control` does not remain live as a separate
+  family. The local record already demoted it to endpoint drift or bottleneck
+  rhetoric unless it returns to the same frozen `I_p^far` inequality. Sources:
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md`
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-009/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- [VERIFIED] Alignment, eigenframe, restricted-Euler, and conditional-regularity
+  labels enter this step as overlap comparators, not as separate survivors.
+  Sources:
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md`
+  - `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/judgments/chain-01.md`
+  - `runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-010-receptionist-search.md`
+
+### 2. Packaging Screen
+
